 <italic class="italic">CRE</italic> (tC year
 <sup class="sup">−1</sup>) represents the volume of annual reduction in carbon emissions due to energy substitution, 
 <italic class="italic">LW</italic> (GJ t
 <sup class="sup">−1</sup>) is the calorific value of wood (14.4) [
 <xref ref-type="bibr" rid="CR44" class="xref">44</xref>], 
 <italic class="italic">EO</italic> (tC kl
 <sup class="sup">−1</sup>) is the carbon emissions volume accompanying the combustion of heavy oil (0.739) [
